definitions.definition: Describing text or other material of a standard or routine nature.
examples: The contract contained all the usual boilerplate clauses.

definitions.definition: Used to refer to a non-functional spacecraft used to test configuration and procedures.
examples: A boilerplate spacecraft was used to test the rocket.

main_definition: Describing text or other material of a standard or routine nature.
